00:31:04,140 --> 00:31:06,860
I mentioned it at the very top of the show, the forgetting argument.

436
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:07,800
Oh, yes.

437
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:10,180
Human memory is notoriously leaky.

438
00:31:11,020 --> 00:31:19,900
In the middle of a massive heated argument with your spouse, you might realize you have completely forgotten the specific comment that started the fight 20 minutes ago.

439
00:31:20,900 --> 00:31:25,080
Culturally, we view that as a biological failure, a lapse in concentration.

440
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:30,920
But if I apply Fliction's framework to my own brain, my forgetfulness isn't a flaw.

441
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:35,580
My brain is acting as a minimal gluing obstruction estimator.

442
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:39,300
That is actually a profoundly deep application of the math.

443
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:40,380
Think about it.

444
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,700
The argument evolved.

445
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:47,000
The emotional constraints, the phi of the room, changed dramatically over 20 minutes.

446
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:53,300
The original comment that started the fight belongs to an outdated homotopy class.

447
00:31:53,700 --> 00:31:54,460
It no longer fits.

448
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:54,820
Right.

449
00:31:55,060 --> 00:32:03,280
If my brain tries to recall it and mathematically glue it to the current screaming match, it creates a massive cognitive obstruction.

450
00:32:04,060 --> 00:32:10,040
So my brain, trying to prevent a total collapse of S, just discards the history.

451
00:32:10,620 --> 00:32:14,720
I forget the start of the fight so I can successfully process the current moment.

452
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:17,240
The neuroscience deeply aligns with this.

453
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:22,740
Human working memory is strictly capacity limited and heavily recency biased.

454
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:31,040
It is enforcing a locality constraint to prevent your cognitive state space from becoming computationally intractable.

455
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:40,480
Your brain is retaining only the portion of the conversational trajectory that still physically fits within the current admissible constraints of your emotional state.

456
00:32:40,780 --> 00:32:44,000
My forgetfulness is just mathematical self-preservation.

457
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,240
That is incredible.

458
00:32:45,240 --> 00:33:04,680
But as mind-bending as it is to apply this to AI and human arguments, Fliction takes these exact same tools, the tartan patches, the gluing obstructions, the homotopy classes, and they aim them at the ultimate target, space-time itself.

459
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:13,940
This is where the paper transitions from a brilliant unifying theory of complex systems into a fundamental rewrite of cosmology.

